{"title_page": "Kasarani", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|official_name          =Kasarani\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        =\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = Kasarani_sidestreet_2015.jpg\n|image_alt             = A typical side street in Kasarani, Nairobi, Kenya.\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = \n|pushpin_map            =Kenya\n|pushpin_label_position =bottom\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location in Kenya\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       ={{flag|Kenya}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Kenya|County]]\n|subdivision_name1      =[[Nairobi County]]\n|subdivision_type2      = \n|subdivision_name2      =\n|subdivision_type3      = \n|subdivision_name3      = \n|subdivision_type4      = \n|subdivision_name4      = \n<!-- Politics ----------------->\n|government_footnotes   =\n|government_type        =\n|leader_title           =\n|leader_name            =\n|established_title      =  <!-- Settled -->\n|established_date       = \n<!-- Area    --------------------->\n|area_magnitude         = \n|unit_pref                =Imperial <!--Enter: Imperial, if Imperial (metric) is desired-->\n|area_footnotes           =\n|area_total_km2           = \n|area_land_km2            = <!--See table @ Template:Infobox Settlement for details on automatic unit conversion-->\n<!-- Population   ----------------------->\n|population_as_of               = 2014 Estimate\n|population_footnotes           =\n|population_note                =\n|population_total               =200000  \n|population_density_km2         =\n<!-- General information  --------------->\n|timezone               = [[East Africa Time|EAT]]\n|utc_offset             = +3\n|timezone_DST           = \n|utc_offset_DST         = \n|coordinates            = {{coord|01|13|44|S|36|54|16|E|region:KE|display=inline}}\n|elevation_footnotes    =  <!--for references: use <ref> tags-->\n|elevation_m            = \n|elevation_ft           = <!-- accord. to Google Earth-->\n|blank_name_sec1        = [[K\u00f6ppen climate classification|Climate]]\n|blank_info_sec1        = [[Tropical monsoon climate|Am]]\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -------->\n|postal_code_type       =  <!-- enter ZIP code, Postcode, Post code, Postal code... -->\n|postal_code            =\n|area_code              =\n|blank_name             =\n|blank_info             =\n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Kasarani''' is a [[residential area]] in [[Nairobi]], the capital city of [[Kenya]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/1%C2%B013'44.0%22S+36%C2%B054'16.0%22E/@-1.2294038,36.9047877,15z/data=!4m2!3m1!1s0x0:0x0|title=Location of Kasarani At Google Maps|last=Google| first=.|publisher=[[Google|Google Maps]]|accessdate=21 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Location==\nThe neighborhood is located along the [[Thika Road]], approximately {{convert|16|km|mi}}, by road, northeast of Nairobi's [[central business district]].<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=21 March 2015| url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Kenya_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Nairobi%2C%20Kenya&toplace=Kasarani%2C%20Nairobi%2C%20Kenya%2C&dt1=ChIJp0lN2HIRLxgRTJKXslQCz_c&dt2=ChIJuyu6qJsVLxgRje0nA3541PM|\npublisher=Globefeed.com|title=Road Distance Between Downtown Nairobi And Kasarani With Map}}</ref>\n\n==Naming==\nIt is thought that the name \"Kasarani\" originated from a river that flows through the area which has the [[Gikuyu language|Kikuyu]] name \"Gathara-ini\" River. \n\n==Population==\nKasarani's population is estimated to be in excess of 200,000, as at March 2015.{{fact|date=March 2015}}. The neighborhood is subdivided into various [[Ward (country subdivision)|wards]], which include Roysambu, Mwiki, Hunters and Warren. Kasarani lies mostly within the [[Kasarani Constituency|Kasarani parliamentary constituency]] in [[Nairobi County]].<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=21 March 2015|first= Lucianne| last=Limo|url=http://www.standardmedia.co.ke/thecounties/article/2000106735/voter-wants-kasarani-mp-john-njoroge-chege-removed-from-office|date=12 March 2014|newspaper=[[The Standard (Kenya)]]| title=Voter Wants Kasarani MP John Njoroge Chege Removed From Office}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|accessdate=21 March 2015| url=http://www.nation.co.ke/counties/nairobi/Thugs-raid-Kasarani-MP-Njoroge-Chege-home-steal-car/-/1954174/2658698/-/ubwimlz/-/index.html|title=Thugs Raid Kasarani MP Njoroge Chege\u2019s Home And Injure Guard|date=19 March 2015 |last=Stella Cherono|first=and Angira Zadock|newspaper=[[Daily Nation]] (Nairobi)}}</ref> It borders [[Juja Constituency]] in Kiambu county.\n\n==Sports==\nKasarani is home to the [[Moi International Sports Centre]], named after former President [[Daniel arap Moi]]. The sports complex has a stadium, gymnasium, swimming pool and hotel. The stadium is used by the [[Kenya national football team|Harambee Stars]] for international matches, and is the home stadium of [[Mathare United]] and [[Tusker F.C.]] of the [[Kenyan Premier League]]. \n\nThe indoor arena is used for volleyball, and is the home venue for the [[Kenya women's national volleyball team]].\n\n==Notable landmarks==\nKasarani is home to the [[USIU Africa]] and [[Pan African Christian University]] campuses. The [[SportView Hotel]] and [[Safari Park Hotel]] are also found here. The area also has the Thika Road Mall (TRM), a shopping complex off the [[Thika Road]] highway.\n\n==Notable Businesses==\n\nKasarani is home to many enterprises. Kasarani is served by several shopping mails such as Mountain Mall, Thika Road Mall (TRM) and Garden City. Super Markets within the area include [[Naivas Limited|Naivas]], Powerstar [[Kassmatt Supermarket]].  [[Www.kasaraniportal.co.ke|Kasarani Portal]], an enterprise listing businesses in Kasarani is located in Seasons Estate. Evib Sports Science, a great fitness center on Mwiki Road offers programs from Strength Training and Cardio to Sauna and Toning Tables\n\n==See also==\n* [[Githurai]]\n* [[Kahawa]]\n* [[Dandora]]\n* [[Ongata Rongai]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.usiu.ac.ke/ Website of USIU Africa]\n\n{{coord|01|13|44|S|36|54|16|E|display=title}}\n{{nairobi|state=collapsed}}\n\n[[Category:Suburbs of Nairobi]]\n[[Category:Populated places in Kenya]]\n[[Category:Nairobi]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2015}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!--See the Table at Infobox Settlement for all fields and descriptions of usage-->\n<!-- Basic info  ---------------->\n|official_name          =Kasarani\n|other_name             =\n|native_name            =  <!-- for cities whose native name is not in English -->\n|nickname               = \n|settlement_type        =\n|motto                  =\n<!-- images and maps  ----------->\n|image_skyline          = Kasarani_sidestreet_2015.jpg\n|image_alt             = A typical side street in Kasarani, Nairobi, Kenya.\n|imagesize              = \n|image_caption          = \n|image_flag             = \n|flag_size              =\n|image_seal             = \n|seal_size              =\n|image_map              = \n|mapsize                = \n|map_caption            = \n|pushpin_map            =Kenya\n|pushpin_label_position =bottom\n|pushpin_map_caption    =Location in Kenya\n|subdivision_type       = Country\n|subdivision_name       ={{flag|Kenya}}\n|subdivision_type1      = [[Counties of Kenya|County]]\n|subdivision_name1      =[[Nairobi County]]\n|subdivision_type2      = \n|subdivision_name