us pandemic in French Guiana|French Guiana]]  \n|97\n|1\n|76\n|<ref name=\"JHU\" /><ref name=\"guiana_first_death\"/>\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Guyana}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guyana|Guyana]]\n|66\n|7\n|9\n||<ref name=\"JHU\" />\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Falkland Islands}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Falkland Islands|Falkland Islands]]\n|11\n|0\n|4\n|<ref name=\"JHU\" />\n|-\n|{{flagicon|Suriname}} [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Suriname|Suriname]]\n|10\n|1\n|6 \n|<ref name=\"JHU\" /><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.starnieuws.com/index.php/welcome/index/nieuwsitem/58114|title=6 people who were infected, are cured (in Dutch)|website=Star Nieuws|access-date=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n|'''Total'''\n|'''86,521'''\n|'''4,080'''\n|'''37,934'''\n|<ref name=\"JHU\"/>\n|}\n\n=== Argentina ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Argentina|files=0}}\n\n=== Bolivia ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Bolivia}}\n\n=== Brazil ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Brazil}}\n\n=== Chile ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Chile|files=0}}\n\n=== Colombia ===\n{{Excerpt|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Colombia|files=0}}\n\n=== Ecuador ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Ecuador}}\n[[File:COVID-19 Outbreak Cases in Ecuador.svg|thumb|Confirmed Covid-19 cases in Ecuador]]\nOn 29 February, the Minister of Health in Ecuador, Catalina Andramu\u00f1o, confirmed the first case of the virus in the country.<ref name=\"ecuador.1\">{{cite web |url=https://mobile.twitter.com/elcomerciocom/status/1233773816825946113 |title=Archived copy |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200302043524/https://mobile.twitter.com/elcomerciocom/status/1233773816825946113 |archive-date=2 March 2020 |access-date=29 February 2020}}</ref>  The patient, a woman in her 70s, Ecuadorian citizen who resides in Spain, had arrived to Guayaquil on 14 February.<ref name=ecuador.1/>\n\nOn 1 March, Andramu\u00f1o announced that five new cases of coronavirus have been confirmed in Ecuador.<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1234238746012397568 |user=elcomerciocom |title=#ATENCI\u00d3N La ministra de Salud, Catalina Andramu\u00f1o, informa cinco nuevos casos positivos de #COVID19 en Ecuador. Los afectados son del c\u00edrculo primario familiar de la paciente. Y se encuentran con sintomatolog\u00eda leve y se mantiene la vigilancia permanente |date=1 March 2020 |language=es}}</ref>\n\nAs of 31 March, there have been 2240 confirmed cases, plus 75 deaths linked to COVID-19. The Health Ministry also reported 61 deaths probably related to Covid-19.<ref>Ministerio de Salud P\u00fablica, [https://www.salud.gob.ec/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Boletin-030-AM_Nacional.pdf Gaceta epidemiol\u00f3gica 030]</ref>\n\nEcuador was described in April as emerging as the \"epicentre\" of the pandemic in Latin America.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stuff.co.nz/national/health/coronavirus/120818001/uncollected-bodies-lie-for-days-in-the-streets-of-ecuador-the-emerging-epicenter-of-the-coronavirus-in-latin-america |title=Uncollected bodies lie for days in the streets of Ecuador the emerging epicentre of the coronavirus in Latin America |publisher= Stuff/Fairfax |date=4 April 2020}}</ref> The [[Guayas Province]] was particularly strongly affect, with thousand of excess deaths reported compared to the figure for a normal period.<ref name=\"bbc ecuador\" /> It was reported on 17 April that 10,939 people had died in six weeks since the start of March in the Guayas Province, compared to a normal figure of 3,000 for the province.<ref name=collyns>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/17/coronavirus-death-toll-in-ecuador-could-be-far-higher-than-thought |title=\nEcuador's death rate soars as fears grow over scale of coronavirus crisis |first=Dan |last=Collyns|date= 17 April 2020 |work=The Guardian}}</ref>\n\n=== French Guiana ===\n{{main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in French Guiana}}\nOn 4 March 2020, the first 5 cases were found the French [[overseas department and region]] of [[French Guiana]], <ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.antiguaobserver.com/five-coronavirus-cases-confirmed-in-french-guiana-march-4-2020/ |title=Five coronavirus cases confirmed in French Guiana March 4, 2020 |website=Antigua Observer |date=4 March 2020 |accessdate=5 March 2020}}</ref> and the first death was announced on 20 April 2020.<ref name=\"guiana_first_death\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.franceguyane.fr/actualite/sante/coronavirus/un-premier-mort-du-covid-19-en-guyane-467580.php |title=Un premier mort du Covid-19 en Guyane|language=fr|website=France Guyane|access-date=20 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Guyana ===\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Guyana}}\nOn 11 March 2020, the first case of coronavirus was recorded in [[Guyana]] from a 52-year-old woman suffering from underlying health conditions, including diabetes and hypertension.<ref>{{cite news |title=Guyana confirms first case of coronavirus in woman who returned from U.S. |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-guyana-confirmed/guyana-confirms-first-case-of-coronavirus-in-woman-who-returned-from-u-s-idUSKBN20Z06B |accessdate=12 March 2020 |work=Reuters |date=12 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref> The woman died at the Georgetown Public Hospital.<ref name = kainews>{{cite news |title=Breaking News! Guyana records first coronavirus-related death |url=https://www.kaieteurnewsonline.com/2020/03/11/breaking-news-guyana-records-first-coronavirus-related-death/ |accessdate=12 March 2020 |work=Kaieteur News |date=11 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Paraguay===\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Paraguay}}\nOn 7 March the first confirmed case in [[Paraguay]] was announced, a 32-year-old Paraguayan who arrived from Ecuador.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/international/paraguay-reports-first-coronavirus-case-811730.html |title=Paraguay reports first coronavirus case |date=8 March 2020 |website=Deccan Herald}}</ref>\n\nOn 10 March, Paraguay suspended public school sessions and large-scale public events for 15 days due to the coronavirus.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/03/10/world/americas/10reuters-health-cornavirus-paraguay.html|title=Paraguay Suspends Public Schools for 15 Days Due to Coronavirus|newspaper=The New York Times|agency=Reuters|date=10 March 2020|accessdate=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 March, Paraguay suspended flights coming from Europe.<ref>{{cite news|url= https://www.abc.com.py/nacionales/2020/03/12/paraguay-suspende-ingreso-de-vuelos-provenientes-de-europa/ |title=Paraguay Suspends Flights from Spain Due to Coronavirus|newspaper=ABC Color|agency=ABC|date=13 March 2020|accessdate=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Peru===\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Peru}}\nOn 6 March the first confirmed case in [[Peru]] was announced.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/health-coronavirus-peru-idUSE6N29R02T |title=Peru records first confirmed case of coronavirus, President Vizcarra says |date=6 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=6 March 2020 |via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n\n===Suriname===\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Suriname}}\nOn 13 March 2020, [[Vice President of Suriname|Vice President]] [[Ashwin Adhin]] announced the first confirmed case in the country.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-suriname-confirmed/suriname-confirms-first-coronavirus-case-authorities-will-close-borders-idUSKBN210373?feedType=RSS&feedName=businessNews |title=Suriname confirms first coronavirus case, authorities will close borders |date=13 March 2020 |work=Reuters |access-date=13 March 2020 |via=www.reuters.com}}</ref>\n\nOn 3 April 2020, the first death was announced. <ref name=\"suriname_death\">{{Cite news|url=https://covid-19.sr/suriname-noteert-eerste-covid-19-dode/| title=Suriname confirms first death|website=COVID SURINAME|access-date=4 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n===United Kingdom===\n====Falkland Islands====\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in the Falkland Islands}}\nOn 3 April 2020, the Falkland Islands confirmed its first case.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/FalklandsinUK/status/1246169936105541632|title=A case of coronavirus #COVID19 has been confirmed in the #FalklandIslands. An inpatient in the #Falklands hospital who is in isolation has tested positive for the virus. The patient was admitted from the Mount Pleasant Complex on 31 March with a range of COVID19 like symptoms.pic.twitter.com/KNE5nRnCYf|last=FalklandsinUK|date=2020-04-03|website=@FalklandsinUK|language=en|access-date=2020-04-03}}</ref> Furthermore, as a precaution, the islands' government has closed all schools and nurseries until 4 May.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://en.mercopress.com/2020/03/26/falkland-islands-new-stage-in-government-covid-19-response|title=Falkland Islands: New stage in Government COVID-19 response|publisher=Merco Press|date=26 March 2020|access-date=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Uruguay===\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Uruguay}}\nOn 13 March 2020, the Public Health Ministry announced the first four confirmed cases in the country.\nThe number was updated to 29 on 3/16, to 50 on 3/17 and to 79 on 3/18<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elpais.com.uy/informacion/politica/vivo-gobierno-anuncia-ultimas-novedades-acerca-coronavirus.html|title=Gobierno anunci\u00f3 que hay 79 casos de coronavirus en Uruguay|website=Diario EL PAIS Uruguay|accessdate=26 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n=== Venezuela ===\n{{Main|2020 coronavirus pandemic in Venezuela}}\nOn 13 March 2020, [[Vice President of Venezuela|Vice President]] [[Delcy Rodr\u00edguez]] announced the first two confirmed cases in the country.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ntn24.com/america-latina/venezuela/regimen-de-maduro-confirma-dos-primeros-casos-de-coronavirus-120128 |title=R\u00e9gimen de Maduro confirma dos primeros casos de coronavirus |date=13 March 2020 |website=NTN24.com |language=es |access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 14 March, Communication Minister [[Jorge Rodr\u00edguez (politician)|Jorge Rodr\u00edguez]] informed that eight new cases were detected in the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://elpitazo.net/politica/jorge-rodriguez-confirma-ocho-nuevos-casos-de-coronavirus-en-venezuela/|title=Suben a 10 los casos por coronavirus en Venezuela|last=Torrealba|first=Diego|date=14 March 2020|website=[[El Pitazo]]|language=Spanish|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nOn 26 March, the first death was reported.<ref name=Reutersfirstdeath>{{Cite news|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-coronavirus-venezuela-death-idUSKBN21D3Q3|title=Venezuela confirms first coronavirus death: official|date=26 March 2020|work=Reuters|access-date=27 March 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Prevention in other countries and territories==\n\n===South Georgia & the South Sandwich Islands===\nThe remote territory is uninhabited, save for small communities of scientists; the territory is also occasionally visited by small groups of tourists.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.gs/information/about-sgssi/ |title=About SGSSI \u2013 Government of South Georgia & the South Sandwich Islands |publisher=Gov.gs |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> On 17 March tourist facilities in [[Grytviken]] were closed as a precaution,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.gs/precautionary-measures-at-grytviken |title=Precautionary Measures at Grytviken \u2013 Government of South Georgia & the South Sandwich Islands |publisher=Gov.gs |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref> with various other measures being implemented to protect workers on the islands.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gov.gs/gsgssi-covid-19-update |title=GSGSSI COVID-19 Update \u2013 Government of South Georgia & the South Sandwich Islands |publisher=Gov.gs |date= |accessdate=2020-03-30}}</ref>\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|group=\"lower-alpha\"}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|refs=\n<ref name=\"Minist\u00e9riodaSa\u00fade\">{{cite web |url=https://covid.saude.gov.br/ |title=Casos de coronav\u00edrus no Brasil em 5 de abril |language=Portuguese |work=Minist\u00e9rio da Sa\u00fade |date=5 April 2020 |access-date=5 April 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200324202227/https://g1.globo.com/bemestar/coronavirus/noticia/2020/03/24/brasil-tem-46-mortes-e-casos-2201confirmados-de-covid-19-diz-ministerio-da-saude.ghtml |archive-date=24 March 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[https://coronamap.it Corona MAP] - Daily updated interactive free map of the whole world.  \n*[https://thevirustracker.com/coronavirus-timeline-map Coronavirus Timeline Map] \u2013 Maps the timeline of the Coronavirus infections, deaths and recoveries.\n* [https://www.wolframcloud.com/obj/examples/COVID19World Epidemic data for COVID-19] \u2013 Maps total cases of coronavirus in the world, China and the United States, along with patient data.\n*[https://gisanddata.maps.arcgis.com/apps/opsdashboard/index.html#/bda7594740fd40299423467b48e9ecf6 Coronavirus COVID-19 Global Cases] and [https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19 historical data] by [[Johns Hopkins University]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20200304094209/http://coronamapper.com/ CoronaMapper] \u2013 Map with several updated statistics\n* [https://coronavirus-updates.live/country/south-america Coronavirus Updates] \u2013 Daily updated totals of South America\n\n{{COVID-19|state=expanded}}\n\n[[Category:2020 coronavirus pandemic in South America| ]]\n[[Category:2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic by continent|South America]]\n[[Category:2020 disasters in South America|Coronavirus pandemic]]\n[[Category:Health disasters in South America]]\n[[Category:March 2020 events in South America]]\n[[Category:April 2020 events in South America]]\n", "name_user": "Jonas kam", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2020_coronavirus_pandemic_in_South_America"}
